        <p style="margin-bottom: 0">
          Before 1983, navigating the internet was a challenging and confusing
          task. Users had to memorize long, complex IP addresses to reach
          websites, which made the internet less accessible and user-friendly.
          The introduction of the Domain Name System (DNS) in 1983 fundamentally
          changed the way the internet functioned, making it easier to access
          and navigate. By mapping human-readable domain names (such as
          www.example.com) to numerical IP addresses (such as 192.168.1.1), DNS
          made the internet more intuitive and scalable.
        </p>
      </div>
